defs.docs: Utilities for random number generation

defs.name: distributions
defs.docs: Sampling from random distributions.

defs.name: range
defs.docs: Generating numbers between two others.

defs.name: Range
defs.docs: Sample values uniformly between two bounds.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Create a new `Range` instance that samples uniformly from
 `[low, high)`. Panics if `low >= high`.

defs.name: SampleRange
defs.docs:
The helper trait for types that have a sensible way to sample
 uniformly between two values. This should not be used directly,
 and is only to facilitate `Range`.

defs.name: construct_range
defs.docs:
Construct the `Range` object that `sample_range`
 requires. This should not ever be called directly, only via
 `Range::new`, which will check that `low < high`, so this
 function doesn't have to repeat the check.

defs.name: sample_range
defs.docs:
Sample a value from the given `Range` with the given `Rng` as
 a source of randomness.

defs.name: gamma
defs.docs: The Gamma and derived distributions.

defs.name: Gamma
defs.docs: The Gamma distribution `Gamma(shape, scale)` distribution.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Construct an object representing the `Gamma(shape, scale)`
 distribution.

defs.name: ChiSquared
defs.docs:
The chi-squared distribution `χ²(k)`, where `k` is the degrees of
 freedom.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Create a new chi-squared distribution with degrees-of-freedom
 `k`. Panics if `k < 0`.

defs.name: FisherF
defs.docs: The Fisher F distribution `F(m, n)`.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Create a new `FisherF` distribution, with the given
 parameter. Panics if either `m` or `n` are not positive.

defs.name: StudentT
defs.docs:
The Student t distribution, `t(nu)`, where `nu` is the degrees of
 freedom.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Create a new Student t distribution with `n` degrees of
 freedom. Panics if `n <= 0`.

defs.name: normal
defs.docs: The normal and derived distributions.

defs.name: StandardNormal
defs.docs:
A wrapper around an `f64` to generate N(0, 1) random numbers
 (a.k.a.  a standard normal, or Gaussian).

defs.name: Normal
defs.docs: The normal distribution `N(mean, std_dev**2)`.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Construct a new `Normal` distribution with the given mean and
 standard deviation.

defs.name: LogNormal
defs.docs: The log-normal distribution `ln N(mean, std_dev**2)`.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Construct a new `LogNormal` distribution with the given mean
 and standard deviation.

defs.name: exponential
defs.docs: The exponential distribution.

defs.name: Exp1
defs.docs: A wrapper around an `f64` to generate Exp(1) random numbers.

defs.name: Exp
defs.docs: The exponential distribution `Exp(lambda)`.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Construct a new `Exp` with the given shape parameter
 `lambda`. Panics if `lambda <= 0`.

defs.name: Sample
defs.docs: Types that can be used to create a random instance of `Support`.

defs.name: sample
defs.docs:
Generate a random value of `Support`, using `rng` as the
 source of randomness.

defs.name: IndependentSample
defs.docs: `Sample`s that do not require keeping track of state.

defs.name: ind_sample
defs.docs: Generate a random value.

defs.name: RandSample
defs.docs:
A wrapper for generating types that implement `Rand` via the
 `Sample` & `IndependentSample` traits.

defs.name: Weighted
defs.docs: A value with a particular weight for use with `WeightedChoice`.

defs.name: weight
defs.docs: The numerical weight of this item

defs.name: item
defs.docs: The actual item which is being weighted

defs.name: WeightedChoice
defs.docs: A distribution that selects from a finite collection of weighted items.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Create a new `WeightedChoice`.

defs.name: jitter
defs.docs: Non-physical true random number generator based on timing jitter.

defs.name: JitterRng
defs.docs:
A true random number generator based on jitter in the CPU execution time,
 and jitter in memory access time.

defs.name: NoTimer
defs.docs: No timer available.

defs.name: CoarseTimer
defs.docs: Timer too coarse to use as an entropy source.

defs.name: NotMonotonic
defs.docs: Timer is not monotonically increasing.

defs.name: TinyVariantions
defs.docs: Variations of deltas of time too small.

defs.name: TooManyStuck
defs.docs: Too many stuck results (indicating no added entropy).

defs.name: TimerError
defs.docs: An error that can occur when `test_timer` fails.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Create a new `JitterRng`.
 Makes use of `std::time` for a timer.

defs.name: new_with_timer
defs.docs:
Create a new `JitterRng`.
 A custom timer can be supplied, making it possible to use `JitterRng` in
 `no_std` environments.

defs.name: set_rounds
defs.docs:
Configures how many rounds are used to generate each 64-bit value.
 This must be greater than zero, and has a big impact on performance
 and output quality.

defs.name: test_timer
defs.docs:
Basic quality tests on the timer, by measuring CPU timing jitter a few
 hundred times.

defs.name: timer_stats
defs.docs:
Statistical test: return the timer delta of one normal run of the
 `JitterEntropy` entropy collector.

defs.name: os
defs.docs:
Interfaces to the operating system provided random number
 generators.

defs.name: OsRng
defs.docs:
A random number generator that retrieves randomness straight from
 the operating system. Platform sources:

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Create a new `OsRng`.

defs.name: read
defs.docs: A wrapper around any Read to treat it as an RNG.

defs.name: ReadRng
defs.docs:
An RNG that reads random bytes straight from a `Read`. This will
 work best with an infinite reader, but this is not required.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Create a new `ReadRng` from a `Read`.

defs.name: reseeding
defs.docs:
A wrapper around another RNG that reseeds it after it
 generates a certain number of random bytes.

defs.name: ReseedingRng
defs.docs:
A wrapper around any RNG which reseeds the underlying RNG after it
 has generated a certain number of random bytes.

defs.name: reseeder
defs.docs: Controls the behaviour when reseeding the RNG.

defs.name: new
defs.value: fn (rng: R, generation_threshold: u64, reseeder: Rsdr) -> ReseedingRng<R, Rsdr>
defs.docs: Create a new `ReseedingRng` with the given parameters.

defs.name: reseed_if_necessary
defs.docs:
Reseed the internal RNG if the number of bytes that have been
 generated exceed the threshold.

defs.name: Reseeder
defs.docs: Something that can be used to reseed an RNG via `ReseedingRng`.

defs.name: reseed
defs.docs: Reseed the given RNG.

defs.name: ReseedWithDefault
defs.docs:
Reseed an RNG using a `Default` instance. This reseeds by
 replacing the RNG with the result of a `Default::default` call.

defs.name: seq
defs.docs: Functions for randomly accessing and sampling sequences.

defs.name: sample_iter
defs.value: fn <T, I, R> (rng: &mut R, iterable: I, amount: usize) -> Result<Vec<T>, Vec<T>>
defs.docs: Randomly sample `amount` elements from a finite iterator.

defs.name: sample_slice
defs.value: fn <R, T> (rng: &mut R, slice: &[T], amount: usize) -> Vec<T>
defs.docs: Randomly sample exactly `amount` values from `slice`.

defs.name: sample_slice_ref
defs.value: fn <'a, R, T> (rng: &mut R, slice: &'a [T], amount: usize) -> Vec<&'a T>
defs.docs: Randomly sample exactly `amount` references from `slice`.

defs.name: sample_indices
defs.value: fn <R> (rng: &mut R, length: usize, amount: usize) -> Vec<usize>
defs.docs: Randomly sample exactly `amount` indices from `0..length`.

defs.name: chacha
defs.docs: The ChaCha random number generator.

defs.name: isaac
defs.docs: The ISAAC random number generator.

defs.name: ChaChaRng
defs.docs: A random number generator that uses the ChaCha20 algorithm [1].

defs.name: new_unseeded
defs.docs:
Create an ChaCha random number generator using the default
 fixed key of 8 zero words.

defs.name: set_counter
defs.value: fn (&mut self, counter_low: u64, counter_high: u64) -> ()
defs.docs:
Sets the internal 128-bit ChaCha counter to
 a user-provided value. This permits jumping
 arbitrarily ahead (or backwards) in the pseudorandom stream.

defs.name: IsaacRng
defs.docs: A random number generator that uses the ISAAC algorithm[1].

defs.name: new_unseeded
defs.docs:
Create an ISAAC random number generator using the default
 fixed seed.

defs.name: Isaac64Rng
defs.docs:
A random number generator that uses ISAAC-64[1], the 64-bit
 variant of the ISAAC algorithm.

defs.name: new_unseeded
defs.docs:
Create a 64-bit ISAAC random number generator using the
 default fixed seed.

defs.name: XorShiftRng
defs.docs:
An Xorshift[1] random number
 generator.

defs.name: new_unseeded
defs.docs: Creates a new XorShiftRng instance which is not seeded.

defs.name: Rand
defs.docs: A type that can be randomly generated using an `Rng`.

defs.name: rand
defs.docs:
Generates a random instance of this type using the specified source of
 randomness.

defs.name: Rng
defs.docs: A random number generator.

defs.name: next_u32
defs.docs: Return the next random u32.

defs.name: next_u64
defs.docs: Return the next random u64.

defs.name: next_f32
defs.docs:
Return the next random f32 selected from the half-open
 interval `[0, 1)`.

defs.name: next_f64
defs.docs:
Return the next random f64 selected from the half-open
 interval `[0, 1)`.

defs.name: fill_bytes
defs.docs: Fill `dest` with random data.

defs.name: gen
defs.docs: Return a random value of a `Rand` type.

defs.name: gen_iter
defs.value: fn <'a, T> (&'a mut self) -> Generator<'a, T, Self>
defs.docs:
Return an iterator that will yield an infinite number of randomly
 generated items.

defs.name: gen_range
defs.value: fn <T> (&mut self, low: T, high: T) -> T
defs.docs: Generate a random value in the range [`low`, `high`).

defs.name: gen_weighted_bool
defs.docs: Return a bool with a 1 in n chance of true

defs.name: gen_ascii_chars
defs.docs: Return an iterator of random characters from the set A-Z,a-z,0-9.

defs.name: choose
defs.value: fn <'a, T> (&mut self, values: &'a [T]) -> Option<&'a T>
defs.docs: Return a random element from `values`.

defs.name: choose_mut
defs.value: fn <'a, T> (&mut self, values: &'a mut [T]) -> Option<&'a mut T>
defs.docs: Return a mutable pointer to a random element from `values`.

defs.name: shuffle
defs.docs: Shuffle a mutable slice in place.

defs.name: Generator
defs.docs: Iterator which will generate a stream of random items.

defs.name: AsciiGenerator
defs.docs: Iterator which will continuously generate random ascii characters.

defs.name: SeedableRng
defs.docs:
A random number generator that can be explicitly seeded to produce
 the same stream of randomness multiple times.

defs.name: reseed
defs.docs: Reseed an RNG with the given seed.

defs.name: from_seed
defs.docs: Create a new RNG with the given seed.

defs.name: Open01
defs.docs:
A wrapper for generating floating point numbers uniformly in the
 open interval `(0,1)` (not including either endpoint).

defs.name: Closed01
defs.docs:
A wrapper for generating floating point numbers uniformly in the
 closed interval `[0,1]` (including both endpoints).

defs.name: StdRng
defs.docs:
The standard RNG. This is designed to be efficient on the current
 platform.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Create a randomly seeded instance of `StdRng`.

defs.name: weak_rng
defs.docs: Create a weak random number generator with a default algorithm and seed.

defs.name: ThreadRng
defs.docs: The thread-local RNG.

defs.name: thread_rng
defs.docs:
Retrieve the lazily-initialized thread-local random number
 generator, seeded by the system. Intended to be used in method
 chaining style, e.g. `thread_rng().gen::<i32>()`.

defs.name: random
defs.docs: Generates a random value using the thread-local random number generator.

defs.value: fn <T, I, R> (rng: &mut R, iterable: I, amount: usize) -> Vec<T>
defs.docs: DEPRECATED: use `seq::sample_iter` instead.
